SUMMARY:Alliance Francaise (concert):  Beltuner   (Jazz Fusion/Tango sound
 s!)   $18 
DESCRIPTION:TORONTO ARTS & CULTURE\n**Beltuner is a Paris-based quartet** 
 known for their electrifying live performances and fearless blend of music
 al styles. Since bursting onto the French jazz scene in the early 2000s\, 
 they have built a devoted following with their infectious energy and genre
 -defying sound.\n\nThe group features Johann Riche on accordion and vocals
 \, Pascal Muller on guitar\, Bertrand Allaume on bass\, and Mathieu Stora 
 on percussion. Together\, they create a bold and joyful fusion that draws 
 from swing\, manouche\, musette (small bagpipe)\, tango\, pop\, and contem
 porary jazz.\n\nTicket link is below: $18 per person\n\nRecent performance
  clip--\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iV4TjDMRlC0\n\nAudiences can ex
 pect an exhilarating concert experience\, filled with vibrant soundscapes 
 **and the unmistakable charm of Paris.**\n\n**Ticket link here:**\n\nhttps
 ://www.alliance-francaise.ca/en/art/cultural-season/concerts/288-beltuner\
 n\nOne of our fav venues in Toronto--seating just 140 people.
