SUMMARY:Aga Khan Museum:  Labyrinth Ensemble
DESCRIPTION:TORONTO ARTS & CULTURE\nWe will return to see **Labyrinth Ense
 mble** for the 5th time!\n\n[https://www.labyrinthontario.com/s/stories/la
 byrinth-ensemble-with-efren-lopez-2](https://www.labyrinthontario.com/s/st
 ories/labyrinth-ensemble-with-efren-lopez-2)\n\nEvery FOUR years\, the 14 
 members 'disband'\, and a new group of 14 members is put together. A new c
 ohort!\n\nWhich also means 14 new instruments to learn about!\n\nThe new c
 ohort will dig into European Medieval\, the Eastern Mediterranean\, the Mi
 ddle East\, and Central Asian musical traditions\, and will feature unique
  instrumentation ranging from guzheng\, Hardanger fiddle\, lutes\, hurdy g
 urdy\, qanun and microtonal guitar\; bringing a whole new sound to the pro
 ject.\n\nThe Aga Khan Museum concert venue is one of our top 3 spots in To
 ronto--for live music.\n\nTickets have just gone 'on sale'. I've purchased
  a ticket in Row F.\n\nPrices are: $50 regular. $37.50 for Senior.\n\nhttp
 s://agakhanmuseum.org/whats-on/labyrinth-with-efren-lopez/\n\n\\*\\*\\*Pur
 chase your own ticket--**and the ticket price includes** entry into the Mu
 seum from 6pm onwards (which we always do). We can check out the new exhib
 itions.\n\nIf interested\, grab your own ticket. Don't miss out!\n\nA shor
 t video--3 of the 14 members perform at local Thorncliffe Park festival la
 st summer\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o2XjudW45nQ
